cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.RO

This paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques to predict a complete 3D representation of a scene from RGB-D data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new neural network architecture, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves semantic labeling of the scene, which is related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of 3D space and edge detection also suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.GR (Graphics) or cs.RO (Robotics).
